---
description: Prisma modeling and migration conventions for BetAgent.
globs:
  - "**/schema.prisma"
  - "**/prisma/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Prefer `String @id @default(cuid())`. Never mint composite PKs unless a domain invariant demands it with ADR justification.
- Store vendor identifiers in prefixed columns (`externalSportsId`, `stripeCustomerId`, `supabaseExternalId`, ...).
- Map Prisma models to plural snake_case tables through `@@map("table_name")`.
- Foreign-key fields follow `<entityId>`; timestamps follow `<pastTenseVerb>At` naming.

### Money and numeric precision

- Product pricing fields stay integers in cents.
- Accumulated AI spend fields stay BigInt quantities such as `costUsdMicros`. Never serialize currency math as floats in Prisma enums or JSON payloads.

### Time series plus vectors

- Treat `OddSnapshot` as immutable inserts; forbid updates/deletes unless a remediation script with audit trail executes.
- Partition `odd_snapshots` monthly via hand-authored SQL appended to migrations.
- Default analytics index `(matchId, marketType, selection, capturedAt desc)` plus supporting partial indexes justified per workload ADR.
- Represent embeddings via `Unsupported("vector(1536)")` columns; forbid Prisma-managed writes beyond raw SQL wrappers.
- All similarity lookups pass through audited `prisma.$queryRaw` helpers; create HNSW indexes manually alongside migrations.

### Migrations and seeds

- Run `npm run db:migrate` (wrapping Prisma migrations) locally; CI applies deploy via the same scripted entrypoint tuned for pipelines.
- Layer manual SQL chunks for Postgres extensions (`pgcrypto`, `uuid-ossp`, `vector`), partitioned tables, HNSW, materialized refreshes after Prisma emits its baseline DDL.
- Keep `services/api/prisma/seed.ts` deterministic: seed sports metadata, marquee leagues, curated bookmaker catalog, subscription slabs, bootstrap `AgentVersion`.
